-- 
2011-02-18T10:23:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-18/kazakhstan-boosts-army-spending-17-this-year-president-says.html
  Kazakhstan , the biggest energy
producer in central  Asia , plans to boost defense spending 17
percent this year to increase military wages by 30 percent
starting in July.  The government will spend 200 billion tenge ($1.4 billion)
in 2011 compared with 171 billion tenge last year, President
Nursultan Nazarbayev said during a meeting with Defense Ministry
staff in the capital Astana yesterday. Nazarbayevâ€™s comments
